10. Occurritur autem, etc] Having disposed of the objection urged by the boni viri, Cicero now presents that of the docti et cruditi. The latter involves a charge of inconsistency, because Cicero, while he held mainly to the N ew Academy, which denied the certainty of all knowledge, was nev- ertheless engaged in this discussion of the rules of duty and giving his opinions on philosophical subjects with an appearance of certainty.
